ore up Arctic cooperation in key ways. The conceptually-driven nature of the inquiry makes the book appropriate reading for courses in international relations and political geography, while the carefully selected case studies lend themselves to courses on Arctic politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial sciences. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aArctic Council.  aArctic governance.  aRussia.  acircumpolar.  aenvironmental cooperation.  aindigenous diplomacy.  ainternational relations.  apolitical geography.  apower.1 aWilson Rowe, Elana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526131645zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526131645zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526131645/original  a978-3-11-128277-0 Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA